21:44.919 --> 21:46.354
‐Can you stand?
‐Yes, I can stand.

21:46.388 --> 21:48.593
I'm old, but I'm not an invalid.

21:48.626 --> 21:50.062
‐Oh...
‐Hey, Gail.

21:50.095 --> 21:52.333
Now that you are a vampire,

21:52.366 --> 21:55.740
and we can spend
the rest of eternity together,

21:55.774 --> 21:57.978
there is something
that I would like to ask you.

21:59.515 --> 22:02.621
Gail Marie you‐never‐told‐me‐
your‐last‐name,

22:02.654 --> 22:04.792
would you do me the honor

22:04.825 --> 22:06.496
of being my vampire bride?

22:06.529 --> 22:07.865
(laughing):
Oh, Nandor.

22:07.898 --> 22:10.904
Yeah, I was married before

22:10.937 --> 22:14.043
and it is just...
it's just not for me.

22:14.077 --> 22:15.881
‐(groans)
‐But, hey, you know,

22:15.914 --> 22:18.653
maybe in 30 or 40 years

22:18.686 --> 22:20.790
down the road, who knows?
I mean,

22:20.824 --> 22:23.897
we have all eternity

22:23.930 --> 22:25.901
to figure this out.

22:25.934 --> 22:28.506
‐That's ages, though.
‐Yes. Listen.

22:28.540 --> 22:29.909
Will you wait for me?

22:29.942 --> 22:32.113
‐Yes?
‐Forever.

22:32.146 --> 22:33.550
‐Found your pocketbook.
‐Oh!

22:33.583 --> 22:35.085
All right, guys, I have

22:35.119 --> 22:36.822
